SPANNER NOTATION 
621.93 — Hand Tools (Wrenches, Spanners, Screwdrivers, etc.)
============================================================

1. OPEN‑END SPANNER
   <||>            Open jaws (flat faces)
   <||>__          Offset implied by asymmetry

------------------------------------------------------------

2. RING SPANNER
   [==]--          Closed ring (6/12‑point)
        \_

------------------------------------------------------------

3. COMBINATION SPANNER
   <||>----[==]    Open end + ring end

------------------------------------------------------------

4. ADJUSTABLE SPANNER
   <||>{=}         Movable jaw + adjuster

------------------------------------------------------------

5. SOCKET SPANNER (RATCHET)
   --(O)==[ ]      Ratchet head + socket

------------------------------------------------------------

6. BOX / TUBE SPANNER
   |[]----[]|      Tube body + hex ends

------------------------------------------------------------

7. FLARE NUT SPANNER
   [=/ ]--         Slotted ring for tubing

------------------------------------------------------------

8. RATCHETING SPANNER
   [=>]---         Ring with ratchet pawl direction

------------------------------------------------------------

9. TORQUE WRENCH
   --(O)==[ ]=<T>  Drive head + torque indicator

============================================================
                    QUICK SELECTION GUIDE
============================================================

OPEN-END .......... Fast access, tight spaces, low torque
RING .............. High torque, safest grip
COMBINATION ....... Universal go-to; most mechanics’ default
ADJUSTABLE ........ Multi-size convenience, lower precision
SOCKET/RATCHET .... Speed + torque + reach
BOX (TUBE) ........ Deep recess, spark plugs, long studs
FLARE NUT ......... Tubing lines (brake/fuel/hydraulic)
RATCHETING ........ High-speed tightening in confined areas
TORQUE WRENCH ..... Precision torque requirements

